[SN]TITLE[SN]
Steve Backshall: 'Whales shouldn't be in captivity'

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
SeaWorld in the US state of California has said it will make changes to its shows involving killer whales.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
11 November 2015 Last updated at 06:36 GMT
It follows years of pressure from campaigners who say the the animals don't belong in captivity.
SeaWorld say they work hard to look after their killer whales and treat them well.
But campaigners say orcas just don't belong in captivity.
CBBC wildlife presenter Steve Backshall, gave us his thoughts...
